    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-06-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-07-07T14:56:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Creating Capacity for Communities in Need Act</b></p> <p>This bill provides for an exception, during the national emergency relating to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019), to provisions under the Stark law (i.e., the Physician Self-Referral Law) that prohibit physician-owned hospitals from expanding facility capacity. </p> <p>Specifically, the bill excludes from such restrictions any increase in operating rooms, procedure rooms, or beds for which a hospital is licensed or begins construction during the period of March 13, 2020, through the last day of the national emergency. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
